wikipedia_page.main: Graeme Landels (born in Broxburn) is a footballer who played for Raith Rovers as a midfielder, making his debut league appearance against Celtic in the 1995-96 season. After leaving Rovers, Landels went on to play for Whitburn, winning the Scottish Junior Cup in 1999-00, and Linlithgow Rose again winning the Scottish Junior Cup in 2001-02. After securing the Scottish Cup win for the second time in his career the Linlithgow Rose captain was named Player of the Year by fans and the club's website.
